definition.value: A coumarate that is the conjugate base of 2-coumaric acid.
A member of the class of pyrimidones that is 1,2-dihydropyrimidin-2-one in which the hydrogen at position 4 is replaced by a 5,6-diamino-2-oxo-2,3,4,5-tetrahydropyrimidin-4-yl group.
A dicarboxylic acid dianion resulting from the removal of a proton from both of the carboxylic acid groups of 2-hydroxyglutaric acid.
